            "title": "Shopify's General Counsel Tapped for Operations Chief",
            "description": "<div class=\"txt-s4 article-text\"><p>\n  By Dean Seal </p><br/><p>\n  Shopify said its general counsel has been appointed chief operating officer. </p><!-- Article --><p>\n\n  The e-commerce platform said Thursday that it has tapped Jessica Hertz to take on the COO role that was vacated last month by Kaz Nejatian, who left to become chief executive of Opendoor Technologies. </p><p>\n\n  Hertz joined Shopify in 2021 and had served as general counsel until now. Before that, she served for nearly a year as White House staff secretary for the Biden administration. </p><p>\n\n  Write to Dean Seal at dean.seal@wsj.com </p><br/><p>\n  (END) Dow Jones Newswires</p><p>\n\n  10-09-25 1641ET</p></div>",
